    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n5190" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κεῖμαι</span></b> , <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κεῖσαι, κεῖται</span>, 3 pl. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κεῖνται,
            κέαται, κείαται</span>, subj. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κῆται</span>, imp. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κεῖσο,
          κείσθω</span>, inf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κεῖσθαι</span>, part.
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κείμενος</span>, ipf. (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐ</span>)<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κείμην</span>, 3
          pl. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κέατο, κείατο</span>, iter. 3 sing.
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κέσκετο</span>, fut. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κείσομαι</span>: <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">lie, be placed</span> or
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">situated</span>, of both persons and things, and often
          virtually a pass. to <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">τίθημι</span>, as
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κεῖται ἄεθλα</span>, prizes ‘are offered,’
            <i><span class="en">Il. 23.273</span></i>; freq. where we say
          ‘stand,’ <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">δίφρος, θρῆνυς</span>, <i><span class="en">Od. 17.331</span></i>, 410; fig., <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">πένθος ἐπὶ φρεσὶ κεῖται,</span>
          <i><span class="en">Od. 24.423</span></i>; <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">
            ταῦτα θεῶν ἐν γούνασι κεῖται</span>, ‘rest’ in their disposal;
          see <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">γόνυ</span>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
